classDiagram
    title Chapter 24: Blockchain and Block Class Structure
    
    class Blockchain {
        -blocks: Vec~Block~
        -difficulty: u32
        +new() Blockchain
        +add_block(data: String)
        +mine_block(block: &mut Block)
        +verify() bool
        +get_latest() &Block
        +get_chain() &Vec~Block~
    }
    
    class Block {
        -index: u64
        -timestamp: u64
        -data: String
        -previous_hash: String
        -hash: String
        -nonce: u64
        +new(index: u64, data: String, prev_hash: String) Block
        +calculate_hash() String
        +mine(difficulty: u32)
        +verify() bool
    }
    
    class HashUtil {
        +sha256(data: &str) String
        +hash_with_nonce(data: &str, nonce: u64) String
        +verify(hash: &str, data: &str) bool
    }
    
    Blockchain "1" *-- "many" Block : contains (Vec)
    Block --> HashUtil : uses for hashing
    Blockchain --> HashUtil : uses for verification
    
    Note over Blockchain: Maintains chain of blocks\nValidates proof of work
    Note over Block: Contains data, hash, prev_hash\nMined with nonce
    Note over HashUtil: SHA256 cryptographic hash\nDeterministic output
